comments:
ReconcileStepForValidator#validate() is setting the wrong path on the IncrementalHelper.

the code is getting the file from the StructuredModel's base location:

	private IFile getFile() {
		IStructuredModel model = null;
		IFile file = null;
		try {
			model = StructuredModelManager.getModelManager().getExistingModelForRead(getDocument());
			if (model != null) {
				String baseLocation = model.getBaseLocation();
				// The baseLocation may be a path on disk or relative to the
				// workspace root. Don't translate on-disk paths to
				// in-workspace resources.
				IPath basePath = new Path(baseLocation);
				if (basePath.segmentCount() > 1 && !basePath.toFile().exists()) {
					file = ResourcesPlugin.getWorkspace().getRoot().getFile(basePath);
				}
			}
		}
		finally {
			if (model != null) {
				model.releaseFromRead();
			}
		}
		return file;
	}

It appears that the base location has no indication that the actual file came from a jar, it shows up as simply being a file in the project.

We should be checking file.exists(), if not, don't try to validate.  The file should be non-editable anyway, so validation doesn't make much sense.

checked this fix into HEAD.
